description:
&lt;p&gt;Full Time 37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to expand our dynamic and motivated Ultrasound team and are inviting hard working and enthusiastic Sonographers to apply for a job with us at Swansea Bay University Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The multidisciplinary ultrasound team at Swansea have an outstanding reputation for the services provided, where the Sonographer team undertakes a comprehensive range of ultrasound examinations that includes Abdominal, Gynaecological, Obstetric, Vascular, MSK and sonographer led acute imaging.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post available would suit experienced hard working sonographers who are interested in developing both clinical and leadership skills. We are looking for professional individuals who are forward thinking with great patient and team working skills. All candidates must have a suitable graduate qualification in Medical Ultrasound (PgC, PgD, MSc) and have current professional registration (HCPC/NMC). FMF Nuchal Accreditation is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All of our ultrasound rooms are currently equipped with GE Voluson and Canon units. There are 3 rooms in antenatal clinic, 3 general rooms and a satellite early pregnancy unit/acute gynae suite. Within our Obstetric ultrasound department, we also have slave monitors in every room.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have the skills we are looking for or would like to broaden those you already have, then we look forward to hearing from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Delyth Pirotte Superintendent Sonographer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Delyth.pirotte@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01792 285467&lt;/p&gt;
